headline: CarMax Sacks CEO and Slashes Outlook
summary: CarMax terminated Chief Executive Bill Nash, as the board expressed disappointment in the used-car retailer's performance, while rival Carvana enjoys strong growth and record profit. Nash, who has led CarMax since 2016, will be replaced by board member David McCreight, who will take over next month as interim president and CEO.
